sequenceDiagram
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod<br/>ZMQ PUB 5557/TCP
    participant ZMQ as ZMQ Subscriber<br/>zmqSubscriber
    participant Pool as kvevents.Pool<br/>Sharded Workers
    participant Adapter as EngineAdapter<br/>(vLLM/SGLang)
    participant Index as kvblock.Index<br/>(InMemory/Redis)
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PodRecon as Pod Reconciler<br/>controller-runtime
    participant SubMgr as SubscriberManager
    participant Scheduler as Inference Scheduler<br/>/ EPP
    participant Indexer as kvcache.Indexer
    participant TokPool as tokenization.Pool
    participant UDS as UDS Tokenizer<br/>gRPC over UDS
    participant TokProc as TokenProcessor<br/>CBOR+FNV-64a
    participant Scorer as KVBlockScorer

    Note over K8s,SubMgr: Flow 3: Pod Discovery (ZMQ Subscriber Management)
    K8s->>PodRecon: Watch pods (label: llm-d.ai/inferenceServing=true)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, TLS, SA Token
    PodRecon->>SubMgr: EnsureSubscriber(podIP)
    SubMgr->>ZMQ: Start ZMQ SUB<br/>tcp://<PodIP>:5557

    Note over vLLM,Index: Flow 1: KV-Cache Event Ingestion (Write Path)
    vLLM->>ZMQ: KVEvents (BlockStored, BlockRemoved, AllBlocksCleared)<br/>ZMQ PUB/SUB 5557/TCP, msgpack
    ZMQ->>Pool: AddTask (FNV-1a hash routes to worker)
    Pool->>Adapter: ParseMessage (msgpack decode)
    Adapter-->>Pool: Parsed KVEvent
    alt InMemory Backend
        Pool->>Index: Add/Evict blocks (in-process)
    else Redis/Valkey Backend
        Pool->>Index: Add/Evict blocks<br/>6379/TCP, Redis protocol, optional TLS
    end

    Note over Scheduler,Scorer: Flow 2: KV-Cache Scoring (Read Path)
    Scheduler->>Indexer: GetPodScores(prompt) [in-process library call]
    Indexer->>TokPool: Tokenize(prompt)
    TokPool->>UDS: gRPC Tokenize RPC<br/>UDS socket /tmp/tokenizer/tokenizer-uds.socket<br/>No encryption, No auth
    UDS-->>TokPool: Token IDs
    Indexer->>TokProc: TokensToKVBlockKeys<br/>CBOR canonical encoding + FNV-64a hash
    TokProc-->>Indexer: Block Keys (hash chain)
    alt InMemory Backend
        Indexer->>Index: Lookup block keys (in-process)
    else Redis/Valkey Backend
        Indexer->>Index: Lookup block keys<br/>6379/TCP pipelined
    end
    Index-->>Indexer: Pod → block matches
    Indexer->>Scorer: Score(pod matches, block positions)
    Scorer-->>Indexer: Pod scores (cache hit ratio)
    Indexer-->>Scheduler: Scored pod list (sorted by KV-cache reuse)
